    </td><td width="100%" valign="top"><h1 align="center"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a name="top"></a> Mission
          Statement</font></h1>
      <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Beyond
          Broadcast&trade; works across media to create unique arts
          experiences that challenge and inspire.</font>
      <p align="center"><strong><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Ways
      of Seeing </font></strong>
      <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The
          language of traditional filmmaking is open to innovation. Here are
          some programs and projects created by BB&trade; with adventuresome partners
          and in different media:</font>
      <p align="justify"><span class="style7">T</span><span class="style9"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">HE
          </font></span><span class="style7">S</span><span class="style9"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">CARLET
          </font></span><span class="style7">L</span><span class="style9"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">ETTER</font></span><strong><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> <img src="images/SL%20duo%20MOD2%20color.jpg" width="101" height="83"></font></strong>      
      <p align="center" class="style6">THE PERFORMANCE LAB <img src="images/RISA-STAR!!!.jpg" width="101" height="76"> 
      <p align="justify" class="style6">
      <p align="left" class="style10">WHITMAN<img src="images/WHITMAN%202%20MOD3.jpg" width="113" height="92"> <br>
        <br>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="style21"> Arts on 2<img src="images/A2%20LOGO%20MOD1.jpg" width="101" height="83"> </span>
      <p align="left" class="style15"><em>The Living</em>:<span class="style16"> <img src="images/LT%20aghast%2012%20MOD%201.jpg" width="101" height="83"><br>
        Seven
          Meditations on Political Sado-Masochism </span>
      <p align="center" class="style17"> Lamb
        Chop's <br>
        Sing-a-Long <img src="images/SHARI%203%20MOD2A.jpg" width="180" height="136">Play-a-Long!        
      
      <p align="center" class="style12">1996-2006
      <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">BB&#153; is
        a lead member of </font><span class="style11">THE PERFORMANCE LAB </span><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> [formerly
        DancePartners</font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="style18">&copy;</span></font><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">],
        one of a handful of arts projects funded by a major grant from the Technology
        Opportunities Program [US Department of Commerce]. </font><span class="style11">TPL</span><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">,
        using existing interactive technology, has the mandate to create a national
      model for teaching &amp; coaching The Performing Arts. </font>      
      <p align="center"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://www.theperformancelab.org/">The
        Performance Lab</a></font></td>
  </tr>
